  "What does 'lurking variable' mean in the context of correlation?": "",
  "A variable that is explicitly plotted as one of the axes on the scatterplot display": "",
  "The response variable that is being predicted or explained in the research study": "",
  "A variable that has no variation and remains constant across all observations": "",
  "An unmeasured variable that may influence both variables being studied, creating a misleading correlation": "",
  "A lurking variable is not included in the analysis but affects both observed variables, potentially creating a spurious correlation.": "",
